{
  "texts": [
    "This advantage is also reflected in the scoring evaluation, where RARO consistently surpasses baselines (e.g., 67.8 vs. 53.7 for SFT at 1.5B).",
    "Notably, RL-Logit, leading baseline for DeepMath, fails to produce competitive results, yielding near-zero improvement over the base model (0.364 vs. 0.350 at 1.5B) for both the win-rate and scoring evaluation.",
    "This suggests that standard preference optimization methods and RL-based approaches struggle to generalize in open-ended domains.",
    "Scaling Creative Capabilities.",
    "A key result is the scalability of RARO with model size in the creative domain."
  ]
}